    "In many other cases, the MT systems do not produce translation errors but consistently opt for gender stereotypical translations such as the French 'tu es belle [feminine]' as a translation for the English gender-neutral 'you are beautiful [neutral]' (where the English sentence is besides gender, also ambiguous in terms of number and degree of politeness as opposed to French) and 'tu es intelligent [masculine] ' as a translation for the English sentence 'you are smart [neutral] '."
